Open Fabric APIs, v1

Authentication

Request access token

Request Body schema: application/x-www-form-urlencoded
grant_type
required
string
Value: "client_credentials"
scope
string

Requested scopes for this access token, separated by whitespace. If not provided, all available scopes of the client will be requested. For the list of available scopes, please refer to the API Access Scopes document.

Responses

Sandbox

https://auth.sandbox.openfabric.co/oauth2/token

Development

https://auth.dev.openfabric.co/oauth2/token

Production

https://auth.openfabric.co/oauth2/token

Request samples

  • Payload
Content type
application/x-www-form-urlencoded
grant_type=client_credentials&scope=resources%2Ftransactions.create%20resources%2Ftransactions.read

Response samples

  • 200
Content type
application/json
{
  • "access_token": "eyJz9sdfsdfsdfsd",
  • "id_token": "dmcxd329ujdmkemkd349r",
  • "token_type": "Bearer",
  • "expires_in": 3600
}

Tenant: Transaction Orchestration

Approve / Decline a transaction

Tenant can call this API to approve or fail a transaction.

Request Body schema: application/json
required

Open Fabric will create a Transaction with the default state created. Tenant can update the transaction to approved or failed.

tenant_reference_id
required
string >= 4 characters ^[a-zA-Z0-9\-_@\.]*$

Transaction ID in Tenant system. This is the same transaction ID that Tenant shared as part of the above step

status
required
string (TransactionApprovalStatus)
Enum: "approved" "failed"

Tenant can either Approve or Fail a transaction. In case of Failed, reason is mandatory.

approved_amount
number

Approved transaction amount

approved_currency
string = 3 characters ^[A-Z]*$

Approved transaction Currency (ISO 4217 Alpha-3 currency codes)

reason
string

Responses

Sandbox

https://api.sandbox.openfabric.co/v1/tenants/transactions

Development

https://api.dev.openfabric.co/v1/tenants/transactions

Production

https://api.openfabric.co/v1/tenants/transactions

Request samples

  • Payload
Content type
application/json
Example
{
  • "tenant_reference_id": "cd992711-498f-47be-b636-cf2e3eaad935",
  • "status": "approved"
}

Response samples

  • 400
  • 500
Content type
application/json
{
  • "error_code": "string",
  • "message": "string",
  • "details": [
    • {
      • "error_code": "string",
      • "message": "string",
      • "param": "string"
      }
    ]
}

Create a transaction

This will be called by Partner to initialize a transaction before interacting with payment methods

query Parameters
txn_trace_id
string <uuid>

Trace UUID (v4) to follow payment sessions

header Parameters
Idempotency-Key
string

Unique value submitted by the client to ensure idempotent request when creating transaction.

Request Body schema: application/json
required

Transaction object to init

instrument
string
Default: "web_checkout"

Instrument of the transaction request. Can be omitted for the web_checkout transaction request.

tenant_id
string <uuid>

OpenFabric Generated ID for the Tenant of the payment method, only for backward-compatibility. If not provided, it will use the ID of the Tenant linked with Partner.

partner_redirect_success_url
required
string <uri>

Redirect URL Configured by Partner - when transaction is approved by Tenant

partner_redirect_fail_url
required
string <uri>

Redirect URL Configured by Partner - when transaction is denied by Tenant

partner_reference_id
required
string^[a-zA-Z0-9\-_@\.]*$

Transaction ID set by Partner and sent to OpenFabric

required
object (CustomerInfo)

OpenFabric collects the below customer Info Collection from merchants. We will pass-through the collected info to Tenant

amount
required
number >= 0.01

Transaction amount for which Tenant's authorization is requested

currency
required
string = 3 characters ^[A-Z]*$

Transaction Currency for which Tenant's authorization is requested (ISO 4217 Alpha-3 currency codes)

required
object (TransactionDetails)

Transaction Details sent by Partner.

pg_name
string

Payment Gateway name

pg_publishable_key
string

Payment Gateway's publishable_key

pg_flow
string (PGFlow)
Enum: "tokenization" "charge"

for which flow that Partner would like OF to execute. If it is not set, default to Tokenization

pg_additional_params
object

Additional parameters required in the card tokenization/charge request for the given Payment Gateway

Responses

ZappAuthz: Pay by Account

Real-time debit transactions.

Exchanges the real-time transaction messages to the AHI with the intent of posting a debit amount to the consumer account. The request data is encrypted in accordance with the JWE encryption standard (RFC7516). Refer to the Zapp Platform Message Signing and Encryption Guide for the anatomy of the encrypted payload data and decryption guide.

header Parameters
x-participant-id
required
string [ 1 .. 50 ] characters
Example: 000545

Unique identifier assigned to the participant by Mastercard during onboarding.

x-request-id
required
string [ 1 .. 50 ] characters
Example: 7eab4eab35a542e085add0363a49c035

Each API request has an associated request identifier. It can be used to match the response to the request and used for tracing, troubleshooting and analysis purposes.

x-product-id
required
string [ 1 .. 50 ] characters
Example: PBA

Unique identifier assigned to the product by Mastercard and given to the participant.

idempotency-key
required
string <uuid> [ 1 .. 36 ] characters
Example: 7da7a728-f910-11e6-942a-68f728c1ba70

Unique identifier generated by the Zapp. Mastercard uses this identifier to recognize subsequent retries of the same request and ensure idempotent behaviour by sending the same response without repeating the operation again.

x-jws-signature
required
string [ 1 .. 512 ] characters
Example: eyJhbGciOiJSUzI1NiIsImtpZCI6Ik1LMGlrb1k3NFpNdUhnbncwSG1MNnpSbi9rRT0iLCJpYXQiOiIxNjc1OTYyMjA3IiwiY3JpdCI6WyJpYXQiXX0..XRHc_Q7mp49sr0CDL6Ps97uz4Lhl3XG_--JfeZrkj-4LK-3gzc7HsN0Jq4UjO_NX5ZlVp_tfL_GE1g9-vUT0NCfXmfbBXYEaC9CgFZIoU9F2PBegdZwHHmkDbu-5-t6kd2xo4UhaQ5VP1quWOD5yAs2a6MlQstT1iT-gPIW1teaiz4lgCmqbcTo6umjLKL-QsYvJ53Ngtb5rrF5WWQ1WKpGeq_PP1hGYbxDzcYBNZqGed-dXuGqpkWJ85JENJyOKDoskWM6cgs6OAjrmjTIFQ0qdfal91SUQtzJ49nbAiqMpROh79uYJ024jgtcQ_StqYJyJWYdLeUv1ge-kDJN0fw

JWS detached signature is applied to ensure data integrity.

Request Body schema: application/json
required

Accounts Debit request.

required
object (ZappAuthzMerchant)
required
object (ZappAuthzAcquirer)
object (ZappAuthzAccountHolder)
required
object (ZappAuthzInstrument)
required
object (ZappAuthzTransaction)
object (ZappAuthzOnBehalfService)

Results of validations performed on behalf of the AHI.

object (ZappAuthzAssociatedTransaction)

Identifiers and the processing results of the original transaction to which this transaction is associated. For example, for a reversal transaction, this will include information on the original transaction being reversed. Similarly, for an advice from the MC network, this will include information on the transaction against which the advice was received.

required
object (ZappAuthzProcessingContext)

Information on how the AHI must process the transaction. Perform consumer address verification if requested and respond with verification results.

Reversals or declined advices for reserved or pending transactions.

Exchanges the real-time transaction messages to the AHI to release the reserved or pending amount from the consumer account due to the transaction being reversed or declined by the MC stand-in system. The request data is encrypted in accordance with the JWE encryption standard (RFC7516). Refer to the Zapp Platform Message Signing and Encryption Guide for the anatomy of the encrypted payload data and decryption guide.

header Parameters
x-participant-id
required
string [ 1 .. 50 ] characters
Example: 000545

Unique identifier assigned to the participant by Mastercard during onboarding.

x-request-id
required
string [ 1 .. 50 ] characters
Example: 7eab4eab35a542e085add0363a49c035

Each API request has an associated request identifier. It can be used to match the response to the request and used for tracing, troubleshooting and analysis purposes.

x-product-id
required
string [ 1 .. 50 ] characters
Example: PBA

Unique identifier assigned to the product by Mastercard and given to the participant.

idempotency-key
required
string <uuid> [ 1 .. 36 ] characters
Example: 7da7a728-f910-11e6-942a-68f728c1ba70

Unique identifier generated by the Zapp. Mastercard uses this identifier to recognize subsequent retries of the same request and ensure idempotent behaviour by sending the same response without repeating the operation again.

x-jws-signature
required
string [ 1 .. 512 ] characters
Example: eyJhbGciOiJSUzI1NiIsImtpZCI6Ik1LMGlrb1k3NFpNdUhnbncwSG1MNnpSbi9rRT0iLCJpYXQiOiIxNjc1OTYyMjA3IiwiY3JpdCI6WyJpYXQiXX0..XRHc_Q7mp49sr0CDL6Ps97uz4Lhl3XG_--JfeZrkj-4LK-3gzc7HsN0Jq4UjO_NX5ZlVp_tfL_GE1g9-vUT0NCfXmfbBXYEaC9CgFZIoU9F2PBegdZwHHmkDbu-5-t6kd2xo4UhaQ5VP1quWOD5yAs2a6MlQstT1iT-gPIW1teaiz4lgCmqbcTo6umjLKL-QsYvJ53Ngtb5rrF5WWQ1WKpGeq_PP1hGYbxDzcYBNZqGed-dXuGqpkWJ85JENJyOKDoskWM6cgs6OAjrmjTIFQ0qdfal91SUQtzJ49nbAiqMpROh79uYJ024jgtcQ_StqYJyJWYdLeUv1ge-kDJN0fw

JWS detached signature is applied to ensure data integrity.

Request Body schema: application/json
required

Account Releases request.

required
object (ZappAuthzAcquirer)
object (ZappAuthzAccountHolder)
required
object (ZappAuthzInstrument)
required
object (ZappAuthzReleaseTransaction)
required
object (ZappAuthzAssociatedTransaction)

Identifiers and the processing results of the original transaction to which this transaction is associated. For example, for a reversal transaction, this will include information on the original transaction being reversed. Similarly, for an advice from the MC network, this will include information on the transaction against which the advice was received.

required
object (ZappAuthzReleaseProcessingContext)

Information for the AHI on how to process the request payload. Must be one of: REQUIRES-DECISION: Provide a response with the processing results, whether approved or declined, a partial amount approved if applicable, an authorization code, and what action was taken on the consumer account, that is, whether the transaction amount was posted to the consumer account, along with address verification results if requested. INSTRUCTION: The AHI must debit or credit the funds on the consumer account and acknowledge the processing results as processed. COMPENSATORY-ADVICE: The AHI should only post to reverse the transaction amount on the consumer account if the associated transaction was previously approved and posted to the consumer account.

VTS: Status Notifications

VTS Status Notifications Summary

Handles VTS inbound status notifications for provisioned tokens

query Parameters
apiKey
required
string <= 64 characters

Client-specific API key issued during onboarding. Alphabetic, numeric; maximum 64 characters.

eventType
required
string
Enum: "TOKEN_CREATED" "TOKEN_STATUS_UPDATED" "KEY_STATUS_UPDATED" "TOKEN_REPERSO_ADVICE" "TOKEN_DEVICE_BINDING_APPROVED" "TOKEN_DEVICE_BINDING_DECLINED" "TOKEN_DEVICE_BINDING_DELETED" "CARDHOLDER_STEPUP_APPROVED" "CARDHOLDER_STEPUP_DECLINED"

Event type

header Parameters
x-pay-token
required
string
x-request-id
required
string
Request Body schema: application/json
required
date
required
integer

Event creation timestamp in UTC format. The UNIX_UTC_Timestamp is a UNIX Epoch Timestamp. The value is in seconds.

api
string <= 8 characters

Account Parameter Index (YHHHHCC) value. Applicable for key status update - Replenishment. This data element is utilized during cryptogram generation for KEY_STATUS_UPDATED event.

vProvisionedTokenID
required
string <= 36 characters

Unique ID for token. String. Alphabetic, numeric, and hyphens ( - ), e.g. spaces are not allowed; maximum 36.

vNotificationID
string <= 36 characters

Reperso Notification ID. Present in case of reperso advice. Applicable for Reperso.

clientReferenceID
string <= 80 characters

Client reference identifier. Only sent for the CARDHOLDER_STEPUP_APPROVED event type.

deviceBindingInfo
object

Information regarding device binding. Applicable for device binding.

Pismo

Receive and process pismo notifications

Receive and process Pismo notifications

Request Body schema: application/json
required

Card network notification objects

mti
required
string

Card network request type. Can be used to identify whether the request is an Advice (Standin flow) or not. For more information, see MTI.

network
required
string

Card brand, values can be MASTERCARD or VISA.

org_id
required
string

Issuer org/tenant ID.

account_type
string

Authorization account type.

acquirer_id
string

Purchase acquirer ID.

advice_detail_code
string

Details why the card network issued this advice. This field is only used for Mastercard requests and it represents the value received in DE60 subfield 2 of the specification, if it is present in the card network message.

advice_reason_code
string

Why the card network issued this advice. For messages other than advices, this field is null. In Mastercard requests this field represents the value received in the DE60 subfield 1 of the specification. For Visa requests, this field represents the value received in the F63.4 of the specification.

anti_fraud_http_status_code
string

Status code returned from anti-fraud API endpoint.

arqc_presence
boolean

Authorization Request Cryptogram. Indicates whether the authorization request was performed and the cryptogram information (field 55 of the Card Network specification) was present in the message.

authorization_code
string

An alphanumeric 6-digit code generated for an authorization request that can be used to relate this event to other events associated with the same authorization. For more information, see the Linking authorization events guide.

bin
string

The first 6 or 8 digits of the PAN for the card used in the purchase.

card_hash
string

Hash of card used in the authorization.

correlation_id
string

Pismo generated authorization correlation ID.

cvv2_presence
boolean

CVV2 present in the purchase flag.

denial_code
string

Pismo custom error code, this code identifies which stateless or stateful rule denied the authorization. See Validation codes for authorization events for more information.

duration_ms
number

Time, in milliseconds, spent to finish the authorization process.

entry_mode
string

Purchase entry mode.

error
string

Error that happened when trying to call our distributor API.

host_connected
string

Source IP address for network authorization.

ica
string

Interbank Card Association (ICA) number. The issuer's sign-on ID. An Interbank Card Association Number (ICA) is a four-digit number MasterCard assigns to a financial institution, third party processor, or other member to identify the member in transactions.

incoming_authorization_code
string

Incoming authorization code from acquirer.

incoming_response_code
string

Incoming response code from the acquirer.

installment_data
string

Number of installments of the purchase - Mastercard only.

local_amount
string

Local purchase amount.

local_currency
string

Local currency of the purchase.

mdes_message_type
string

MDES (Mastercard Digital Enablement Service) message type - Mastercard only.

merchant_city
string

Merchant city.

merchant_country
string

Merchant country or state (for USA/CAN).

merchant_name
string

Merchant name.

merchant_type
string

Merchant category code ID.

network_code
string

Type of card used in purchase - Mastercard only.

network_tid
string

Network transaction ID.

origin
string

Identify from where one transaction was issued, if it is from STRIKER('Rebatedor') or migrated from historical data.

pin_presence
boolean

Was PIN used in purchase.

pin_terminal_capability
string

Terminal PIN presence capability - Mastercard only.

pos_cardholder_presence
string

Cardholder presence at POS - Mastercard only.

pos_postal_code
string

POS postal code - Mastercard only.

pos_transaction_status
string

POS transaction status type - Mastercard only.

processing_code
string

Transaction processing code. See Processing codes and transaction types for more information.

replacement_amount
string

Original purchase value. This field is used for partial cancellations - VISA only.

response_code
string

Response code returned to the network.

response_raw
string

Response JSON without sensitive data.

retrieval_reference_number
string

Acquirer assigned document reference number.

secure_indicator
string

Purchase secure indicator.

server_id
string

Customer unique ID for network authorizations sign-on.

settlement_amount
string

Purchase settlement amount.

settlement_currency
string

Purchase settlement currency.

tcp_bytes_written
number

Number of bytes written back to the network.

tcp_error
string

Error that happened when trying to respond to the network.

timestamp
string <date-time>

Event UTC date and time.

token_requestor_id
string

ID assigned by the token service provider to the token requestor. The token requestor ID is required for Card-on-File token request messages - Mastercard only.

track1_presence
boolean

Track1 data presence in the purchase flag.

track2_presence
boolean

Track2 data presence in the purchase flag.

wallet
string

Wallet (Apple Pay, Google Pay ...) used in purchase - Mastercard only.

VTS: Payment Transactions

VTS Payment Transactions Summary

Handles VTS inbound Payment Transactions

query Parameters
apiKey
required
string <= 64 characters

Client-specific API key issued during onboarding. Alphabetic, numeric; maximum 64 characters.

clientAppID
string <= 36 characters

Unique identifier for the client application; required when the relationshipID query parameter is specified. Alphabetic, numeric, and hyphens ( - ), e.g. spaces are not allowed; maximum 36 characters.

relationshipID
string <= 100 characters

The ID identifying the relationship between a token requestor and the caller of this API, which is a token service provider (TR-TSP) with which the token requestor has a relationship. The relationship is defined at the time of onboarding; contact your Visa representative for more information. String. Alphanumeric; maximum 100 characters.

required
string
x-request-id
required
string

required

integer

Event creation timestamp in UTC format. The UNIX_UTC_Timestamp is a UNIX Epoch Timestamp. The value is in seconds.
